institutions digilego lead to express
participation interest by June 30.

Registration
The workshop will take place in Berlin
at a range of locations within the city.
Accommodation specifics are to be
confirmed soon.
Where
Attendance of the workshop is free of
charge. Funds for travel and
accommodation (5 days) are available
from the Digilego project.
Cost
The workshop will start on the
morning of August 29th and end in
the afternoon of September 2,
When
All staff within the partner institutes is
able to attend. Note however that
each institute has a limit on number
of participants (3 to 4). Contact your
local Digilego lead for more info.
Who can attend
Digilego is organizing a virtual field course
development workshop in Berlin from August 29
to Sept. 2.
The aim is to develop a series of open educa-
tional resources that each have use and value
in their own right but also as a larger-scale
resource that can be used as a field session/field
day in an entirely online capacity. Participants

tspan.tspan: will also learn how to create virtual field

text.tspan: Training will be provided on the development of
virtual field trips and will include:
- outdoor video capture
- video processing and basic editing, and
- use of H5P to create open educational
resources.
The workshop will focus on urban geographic and
environmental themes including urban
(re)development and planning, historical, cultural
and social geography, tourism and urban ecology
but other contributions are encouraged.
The workshop will take place in Germanys
capital Berlin which offers a large variety of
urban, suburban and peri-urban locations for
filming. Specific locations and themes for filming
will need to be determined at least three weeks
prior to the workshop to secure filming licenses.
We are interested in bringing a diverse group of
people together to work on creating open
educational resources. We are particularly keen
to involve colleagues who would like to
contribute expertise specific content.
